/-- THEOREM 1: The fundamental det factorisation.
    det(M_K) = ∏ᵢ det(I - γᵢ Σᵢ)

    This is the key theorem: regardless of whether Σ₁,...,Σ_K commute,
    the determinant of the cycle operator factors as a product of
